## Ayat al-Kursi (255)

The **Throne Verse**. Widely considered the most powerful single verse in the Quran. Many Muslims recite it daily.

> *God. There is no god but Him, the Ever-Living, the Sustainer of all existence. Neither drowsiness overtakes Him nor sleep. To Him belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth. Who can intercede with Him except by His permission? He knows what is before them and what is behind them, and they encompass nothing of His knowledge except what He wills. His throne extends over the heavens and the earth, and their preservation does not tire Him. He is the Most High, the Most Great.* (255)

There's nothing to explain here. It's a complete description of God's nature in a single verse: eternal, all-knowing, all-powerful, untiring, beyond everything.

