## Abraham and the King (258)

A brief story. Abraham argues with a king (traditionally identified as Nimrod) who claims to have power over life and death.

Abraham says: *"My Lord gives life and causes death."*

The king says: *"I give life and cause death"* (by pardoning or executing prisoners).

Abraham responds: *"God brings the sun from the East. Bring it from the West."*

The king is left speechless.

