## Abraham and the Birds (260)

Abraham asks God: *"My Lord, show me how You give life to the dead."*

God says: *"Do you not believe?"*

Abraham: *"I do, but I ask so my heart may be reassured."*

God tells him to take four birds, cut them into pieces, scatter them on different mountains, then call them. They come back to him, alive.

This isn't doubt. Abraham already believes. He's asking to *witness* what he already accepts. The Quran treats this as legitimate: wanting to see doesn't mean you don't believe.

